Leonard Edward JOHNSON, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 22353. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. Feb. 21, 1966. Leonard Edward Johnson, for appellant. John C. Ciolino, Asst. U. S. Atty., New Orleans, La., Louis C. LaCour, U. S. Atty., for appellee.

Before TUTTLE, Chief Judge, and JONES and WATERMAN* Circuit Judges.

Of the Second Circuit, sitting by designation.

 PER CURIAM:

The application of the appellant for relief under 28 U.S.C.A. § 2255 was carefully considered and correctly decided by the district court 252 F.Supp. 116. Its judgment is

Affirmed.
